reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Light came packaged well. Has a beautiful sleek design and what I like is that it folds if you don’t want it upright. Has different light settings which light up very well. Easy touch design to turn off/on etc. What I didn’t like too well it comes with a USB cable and I thought I had to charge it and then disconnected from the USB cable and I could use it as it turned out I have to keep the USB cable connected to the light and the walls in order for it to work, I was kind of disappointed about that. I thought that I could just charge it and have it on my desk and then just charge it as need be. But I’m gonna stay because as I said, the design is beautiful and I like the different light settings on it. Oh, and I like the height of it. It is not short nor too high, and you can adjust the arm of the light so you can have it either up or down the arm and you could either have light more concentrate in one area or you can have the arm up where it gives light to the room.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great desk lamp
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to add a little light to my office space. This lamp works great. I only use it for lighting but I like the fact you can also charge stuff with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great desk light
reviews.reviewText: Love so much about this desk light. Light weight, fits in perfectly on my desk, enjoy the 5 different light types or brightness's, the nightlights on the sides are a big perk, I don't use the timer. I would give it a Perfect 5 stars if it was actually a bit brighter. I do love and use it a ton, just kind of thought the brightest mode would be brighter. I love to leave it on all day long to help brighten my paperwork on my desk - I work from home so this helps a ton. I hope it has a long, long life on my desk - working hard.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Elegant desk lamp with small foot print
reviews.reviewText: Like almost everything about this lamp. It's minimalist design doesn't take up much space or overwhelm the desk and the controls are simple and intuitive. Like that it can be titled vertically and provide lighting when in video meetings.It would be nice if the head could swivel left-right and not just up-down.A wireless charging base would be neat, but impossible at the price-point.Would definitely buy again.

reviews.reviewText: I like that I can adjust where I want my light pointed, only thing I’d want differently was if it was 360, but still does the job even without. Love that I can brighten or dim it when I need to.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Really nice, looks like the picture. Doesn't come with charger
reviews.reviewText: Looks exactly like the picture and functions well. The tap is a little sensitive, but no big deal if you plan on leaving it on your desk. Only issue I have is it didn't come with its own charging cord, so I'm gonna have to buy one. Also, the USB-C is only for charging the lamp... my phone charger is USB-C to USB-C so I have to buy a new phone charger that is USB-A to USB-C. It's not a big deal, but for it to be functional in my space I am having to spend an extra $20 on top of the lamp cost... so that's a little unfortunate, but other than that I love it and it works really well.
